{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773482692084,"sessionID":"ses_314328d09ffeHamS8Go5GE0ezF","part":{"id":"prt_cebce438c001VR1Goo52xB8zgz","sessionID":"ses_314328d09ffeHamS8Go5GE0ezF","messageID":"msg_cebce3afa001xlffGoTlRs0yHJ","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01XhgUKVoTCbcXhuGeZQQobW","tool":"bash","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"git add src/lib/state.ts && git commit -m \"feat(wave-state-integrity): add flushState() with integrity verification\n\nAdd flushState() to state.ts that writes state atomically then reads back\nthe file to verify JSON integrity. Performs up to 2 attempts and validates\nthat wave_id and agents array survive the round-trip. Used during shutdown\nto ensure state.json is never left in a partial/corrupt state.\"","description":"Commit flushState addition"},"output":"[feature/wave-state-integrity f98c09c] feat(wave-state-integrity): add flushState() with integrity verification\n 1 file changed, 62 insertions(+)\n","title":"Commit flushState addition","metadata":{"output":"[feature/wave-state-integrity f98c09c] feat(wave-state-integrity): add flushState() with integrity verification\n 1 file changed, 62 insertions(+)\n","exit":0,"description":"Commit flushState addition","truncated":false},"time":{"start":1773482691943,"end":1773482692084}}}}
