{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482871305,"sessionID":"ses_314328d09ffeHamS8Go5GE0ezF","part":{"id":"prt_cebd09d9b002ijcaokCJJq6sJX","sessionID":"ses_314328d09ffeHamS8Go5GE0ezF","messageID":"msg_cebd091d1001WDBOAYtrGU883u","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement the `wave-state-integrity` feature: ensure the wave state file (`.wombo-combo/state.json`) is written correctly and not left in a partial/corrupt state when the user quits the wave monitor (via B key, Q key, or SIGINT/SIGTERM/SIGHUP signals). Add proper cleanup hooks that flush pending state writes before destroying the TUI screen.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Use conventional commits with scope `wave-state-integrity`, commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks` directory — orchestrator handles that\n- Use `bun run build` to verify the build passes before considering the task complete\n- Use `bun dev` (not the global `wombo` binary) for any manual testing\n- Runtime is Bun, not Node. Use Bun APIs where available\n- ESM only, TypeScript strict mode\n- Branch: `feature/wave-state-integrity`, Base: `main`\n\n## Discoveries\n\n1. **State file is already written atomically** via `saveState()` in `state.ts` (write to `.tmp` then `rename`), but there's no verification that the written file is valid JSON after the write.\n\n2. **There are 4 critical shutdown paths** where state must be saved:\n   - TUI `onQuit` callback (Q key pressed while wave is running) — in both `launch.ts` and `resume.ts`\n   - `SIGINT` handler — in both `launch.ts` and `resume.ts`\n   - TUI `stop()` method — called before `screen.destroy()`, previously had no state-save hook\n   - No `SIGTERM`/`SIGHUP` handlers existed previously\n\n3. **TUI `stop()` only tears down the screen** — it does NOT save state or kill agents. Agent cleanup is in `onQuit`. The `stop()` method is also called before mux attach (temporary TUI teardown), so it must not kill processes.\n\n4. **The `onQuit` callbacks call `process.exit(0)` immediately after saving state**, so ensuring state integrity before exit is critical.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed (3 commits made):\n\n1. **`feat(wave-state-integrity): add flushState() with integrity verification`** (commit `f98c09c`)\n   - Added `flushState()` to `src/lib/state.ts` — writes state atomically, then reads it back and verifies JSON integrity (wave_id match, agents array length match). Retries once on failure. Returns boolean success.\n\n2. **`feat(wave-state-integrity): add onBeforeDestroy hook to TUI stop()`** (commit `eccfa47`)\n   - Added `onBeforeDestroy` optional callback to `TUIOptions` interface in `src/lib/tui.ts`\n   - `stop()` now calls `onBeforeDestroy()` (try/catch wrapped) before `screen.destroy()`\n   - Stored the callback in the `WomboTUI` class constructor\n\n3. **`feat(wave-state-integrity): use flushState() in quit/SIGINT handlers`** (commit `deff764`)\n   - Updated `launch.ts` and `resume.ts` to import `flushState` from state.ts\n   - Replaced `saveState()` with `flushState()` in onQuit callbacks and SIGINT handlers\n   - Added `onBeforeDestroy` callbacks to TUI instances in both files\n\n### In Progress (edited but NOT yet committed):\n\n4. **Add SIGTERM/SIGHUP handlers** — Both `launch.ts` and `resume.ts` have been edited to:\n   - Extract shutdown logic into a `gracefulShutdown(signal)` helper function\n   - Register handlers for `SIGINT`, `SIGTERM`, and `SIGHUP`\n   - Include signal name in the \"State saved\" message\n\n### Remaining Work:\n\n5. **Commit the SIGTERM/SIGHUP changes** — files are edited but not committed\n6. **Run `bun run build`** to verify everything compiles\n7. **Fix any build errors** if they occur\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n- **`src/lib/state.ts`** — Added `flushState()` function (committed). Core state persistence module.\n- **`src/lib/tui.ts`** — Added `onBeforeDestroy` hook to `TUIOptions` and `WomboTUI.stop()` (committed). TUI dashboard class.\n- **`src/commands/launch.ts`** — Updated imports, onQuit, SIGINT handler to use `flushState()` (committed). Added SIGTERM/SIGHUP handlers + `onBeforeDestroy` (uncommitted edit).\n- **`src/commands/resume.ts`** — Updated imports, onQuit, SIGINT handler to use `flushState()` (committed). Added SIGTERM/SIGHUP handlers + `onBeforeDestroy` (uncommitted edit).\n- **`src/lib/monitor.ts`** — Read for understanding process lifecycle (not modified).\n- **`src/lib/ui.ts`** — Read for understanding dashboard rendering (not modified).\n- **`src/config.ts`** — Read for `WOMBO_DIR` constant (not modified).\n- **`AGENTS.md`** — Read for project conventions and build commands.","time":{"start":1773482871303,"end":1773482871303}}}
